            {
              "description": "Feature B — array-iteration sub-task body. Renders one copy of `blocks` per element of the upstream array referenced by `items_ref` (which carries exactly one `[*]` boundary, e.g. `extract.tasks[*]`). Inner `blocks` are any TaskBlock variant except a nested Repeater — Input children declare the per-row form schema, display children render with placeholders resolved per row. The engine treats this as a pass-through — the structural shape is statically declared at compile time, the *count* of rows comes from runtime data the compiler stages into `HumanTaskRequest.payload`. Renderer-only; no engine-side semantics beyond accepting and forwarding it.",
              "properties": {
                "blocks": {
                  "items": {
                    "$ref": "#/definitions/TaskBlock"
